  "beats": [
    {
      "text": "Artificial intelligence has a hunger that no memory chip can satisfy. Every time a frontier model processes a single token, it sweeps across hundreds of gigabytes of weights and KV-cache — at trillions of operations per second. Conventional DDR5 is too slow, the bus too narrow. And now the supply chain itself is cracking under the pressure. This is the DRAM Famine.",
