      "text": "The supply sellout is total and global. SK Hynix announced its entire 2026 HBM, DRAM, and NAND production is fully booked — primarily by NVIDIA. Micron said publicly: we are sold out for 2026. Average DRAM prices surged 172 percent through 2025. DDR5 spot prices quadrupled from September 2025 levels. PC prices are expected to rise 15 to 20 percent in the first quarter of 2026. AI is literally eating your RAM.",
