    {
      "text": "Here is the thesis-breaking risk. HBM was designed for training — an extreme memory-bandwidth-intensive workload where you sweep petabytes of activations across a GPU every second. But the AI industry is shifting toward inference: cheaper, faster, edge-deployed generation. Inference is more cost-sensitive than bandwidth-hungry. One projection shows HBM-based chips declining from 65 percent of accelerator shipments in 2022 to just 30 percent by 2027. If this shift accelerates, HBM could be overbuilt for a world that no longer needs it.",
      "speaker": "Analyst",
