    {
      "text": "So — savior or mirage? For today's training clusters, HBM is an unambiguous engineering necessity. Nothing else can feed a Blackwell or Rubin GPU at scale. But the mirage critique is real: the supply chain cannot scale fast enough, cost per bit is extreme, yields are brutal, geopolitical concentration is an existential risk, and the workload shift toward inference may undermine the very demand that justifies the investment. The real question is not whether HBM works. It is whether the world AI is building actually needs it.",
